#### Summary
Since assertj 3.10.0, we get a `java.lang.ClassCastException` when using `assertThat().extracting()` on a `SortedSet`. 
This issue seems to be related to the update done in #1202.
The `Comparator` used is the one from the `SortedSet` to compare the extracted value.

#### Example

```java
package io.test;

import java.util.*;
import org.testng.annotations.Test;

import static java.util.Comparator.*;
import static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;

public class AssertJSortedSetIssue {
    private static class InternalClass {
        private final String m_member;

        private InternalClass(String member) {
            m_member = member;
        }

        private String getMember() {
            return m_member;
        }
    }

    @Test
    public void shouldNotFail() {
        SortedSet<InternalClass> sortedSet = new TreeSet<>(comparing(InternalClass::getMember));
        sortedSet.add(new InternalClass("1"));
        sortedSet.add(new InternalClass("2"));
        sortedSet.add(new InternalClass("3"));

        assertThat(sortedSet).extracting(InternalClass::getMember).containsOnly("1", "2", "3");
    }
}
```
